title: PARACAS+ICA +HUACACHINA (Ballestas Island+Sundboard) Private Tour
description: This full-day tour to Paracas from Lima lets you get out of the city and explore one of Peru's natural wonders. Look out for animals like penguins, sea lions, and dolphins in their natural environment, shred dunes on a sandboard, and enjoy a delicious lunch (own expense) paired with wine and pisco. Your tour includes hassle-free round-trip transport from your hotel or the port.
all_descriptions: This full-day tour to Paracas from Lima lets you get out of the city and explore one of Peru's natural wonders. Look out for animals like penguins, sea lions, and dolphins in their natural environment, shred dunes on a sandboard, and enjoy a delicious lunch (own expense) paired with wine and pisco. Your tour includes hassle-free round-trip transport from your hotel or the port.

ItineraryThis is a typical itinerary for this productStop At:Paracas, Paracas, Ica Regionyou will see the fishing boats of the people around the port, very colorful, the landscape of the ocean with hills make this place very nice.Duration: 1 hourStop At:Islas Ballestas, Paracas 11660 PeruLets explore the experience in the middle of the ocean, admiring the sea lions, penguins, pelicans, exotic birds and the hundreds of hundreds of wild animals... if you are with luck you can see dolphins... this is considerate as a mini Galapagos island by the biodiversity of animalsDuration: 2 hoursStop At:Laguna De Huacachina, Huacachina 11000 PeruEnjoy in the middle of the desert the unique oasis of South America, exploring with the buguies you will see the amazing landscape of the desert with highest dunes in America, if you would like to feel the adrenaline you can practice the sundboarding...Duration: 2 hoursStop At:Ica, Ica, Ica RegionWe will stop in Ica town to have a tasting time of wine and pisco, this is one of the best local areas to enjoy the most important typical drink of Peru. Its also the place that you will have time to have a traditional Lunch.Duration: 2 hours

reviews.title: Incredible Tour and Guides!
reviews.text: Throughout the booking process, KulTour was very responsive and informative. I knew based on our WhatsApp conversations, that the tour was going to be very well put together. Jordan did not disappoint and even exceeded our expectations. We had a great time seeing the Ballestas Island and all of the animals. The lunch at the Pisco distillery was quite good and we had a lot of fun playing drinking games and tasting the various piscos. Lastly, Jordan and the driver (JosÃ©) stayed with us until sunrise at Huacachina. I know it was a long day for them, but they made sure we had a great experience.In fact, I had such a good experience that I ended up booking another tour with KulTour. They were very accommodating, making sure we were happy and understood the plans. They were also flexible and willing to work with our schedule and interests!Jordan is a great guide and genuinely cared that we had a good experience. Even after moving on from Lima, he kept in contact with us and made sure we were informed about potential protests or road blocks for our next destinations. It was reassuring to have this information and was comforting to know that Jordan was always willing to help!Highly recommend!

reviews.title: Incredible customized Huacachina and Paracas tour
reviews.text: Even though the roads were closed the night before due to protests, Jordan made this trip happen in my last day in Peru and we had a blast in my customized private tour. It was a beautiful day, Paracas National Reserve is absolutely gorgeous and unique. Huacachina Oasis didn't disappoint either. Jordan is a great guide and very fluent in English. We had great conversations on our long journey and I ended my trip on an amazing note.
